    { "type": "row", "id": 400, "title": "Extending this dashboard", "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 82 } },
    {
      "id": 401, "type": "text", "title": "How to add panels",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 83 },
      "options": { "mode": "markdown", "content": "### Adding panels\n\n**Datasource UIDs:** `prometheus`, `loki`, `cloudwatch` (eu-west-1), `cloudwatch-edge` (us-east-1), `tempo`.\n\n**Panel-ID convention:** rows are hundreds — `100` ALB, `200` Faro, `300` VPC CNI / DNS, `400` docs. Panels in a row continue from the row ID. Start a new section at the next free hundred (`500`, `600`, …) and keep `gridPos.x/w` on the 24-col grid.\n\n**Where the metrics come from:**\n- **ALB / target groups** → CloudWatch `AWS/ApplicationELB`. Dimensions are **env-specific**: LB `app/k8s-public-f8655bfb7e/78080c3d6ec33605`, faro TG `targetgroup/k8s-monitori-faroprox-25fb7e8eec/…`. Update both when adding a prod overlay.\n- **Faro pipeline** → Prometheus `faro_receiver_*` (scrape job `alloy`); RUM logs/Web-Vitals → Loki `{job=\"faro\"}` (see the **Frontend & RUM** dashboard).\n- **VPC CNI** → Prometheus `awscni_*` (scrape job `aws-node`, pod IP `:61678`).\n- **DNS / node net** → `coredns_*`, `node_network_*`.\n\n**Removed in the EKS migration** (series no longer exist): Traefik `traefik_service_*` / `traefik_tls_*`, Calico `felix_*`, `kubeproxy_sync_*`. Traefik still serves internal IngressRoutes behind its own NLB — add a dedicated section if that path needs visibility (`traefik_entrypoint_*` and CloudWatch `AWS/NetworkELB` are still emitted)." }
    }
  ]
}
